<h2 class="margin-bottom">lxl-tween-adapters</h2>

<p><code>ember-letter-by-letter</code> doesn't come with an animation library of it's own, but rather leaves the choice to you regarding which to use. To select one, simply specify a <code>tweenLibrary</code>. Out-of-the-box, <code>ember-letter-by-letter</code> comes with three light-weight adapters for <code>animejs</code>, <code>popmotion</code>, <code>velocity</code>, and (with limitations) <code>jquery</code>.</p>

<p>Note that if you want to use <code>velocity</code> or <code>popmotion</code>, you will have to install them. Check out the <a href="https://github.com/embersherpa/ember-cli-velocity" target="_blank">ember-cli-velocity</a> and <a href="https://github.com/null-null-null/ember-popmotion" target="_blank">ember-popmotion</a> repos for more info.</p>

{{format-markdown '```hbs
{{ember-lxl
  text="I use anime.js!"
  tweenLibrary="animejs"
  effect=(hash translateY=20)
}}
```'}}

{{#lxl-container}}
  {{ember-lxl
    text="I use anime.js!"
    tweenLibrary="animejs"
    effect=(hash translateY=20)
  }}
{{/lxl-container}}

