<h3>Config</h3>

<p class="margin-top">You can also specify the tween library in your <code>config/environment.js</code>:</p>

{{format-markdown '```js
module.exports = function(environment) {
  var ENV = {
    emberLetterByLetter: {
      tweenLibrary: "popmotion"
    }
  };

  return ENV;
}
```'}}

<h3 class="margin-top">Custom</h3>

<p class="margin-top">If you want to use a different library, you can create your own adapter by:</p>

{{format-markdown '`ember g lxl-tween-adapter my-tween-adapter`'}}

<p>This'll create a simple Ember object with two functions. First, <code>animate</code>. It'll have access to the element, effect, and duration, for you to do with as you will. Secondly, <code>finish</code>, which will recieve an array containing all the letter elements in the <code>ember-lxl</code> tag. This function should terminate any ongoing animations and finish them immediately. Principally, this is for when the user clicks on the tag and the text autocompletes.</p>
